```{r setup, include=FALSE}
knitr::opts_chunk$set(echo = FALSE)
```


This website contains a links to interactive shiny dashboards. All these dashboards have been licensed under an MIT license. You are free to access, reproduce, and edit the code under the terms of the license. **Click on the thumbnail to activate the dashboard**. Each subheading links to the relevant GitHub repository.


# Population dynamics 
### [Population projection matrices](https://github.com/NathanWhitmore/population_projection_matrices)
[![](screenshots/matrix.png){width=80%}](https://reproducible.shinyapps.io/Population_projection_matrix_dashboard/)

 * Assess growth rates of species based on survival & fecundity
 * Draw life history diagrams
 * Project populations through time 
 * Undertake diagnostics
 * Includes teaching material
 

<br/>
<br/>

# eDNA 
### TICI dashboard 
[![](screenshots/TICI.png){width=80%}]()

 * [currently disabled but should be up shortly]


### [eDNA sample checker](https://github.com/NathanWhitmore/eDNA_sample_checker)
[![](screenshots/samplechecker.png){width=80%}](https://reproducible.shinyapps.io/eDNA_sample_checker)

 * Automated detection of common errors (e.g. incorrect coordinates, missing dates, duplicated id numbers)

<br/>
<br/>

# Forestry
### [Intergenerational share valuation](https://github.com/NathanWhitmore/Treeherder_share_valuation)
[![](screenshots/Treeherder_share_valuation.png){width=80%}](https://reproducible.shinyapps.io/treeherder_share_valuation/)

 * Demonstrates how share valuation can be equalised across time
 

<br/>
<br/>

# Spatial
### [Spatial translator](https://github.com/NathanWhitmore/spatial_translator) 
[![](screenshots/spatial_translator.png){width=80%}](https://reproducible.shinyapps.io/spatial_translator/)

 * Change between spatial formats (csv, kml, gpx, and shp)
 * Switch coordinate reference system

<br/>
<br/>

# Temporal
### [Gnomonic time setting](https://github.com/NathanWhitmore/sundial/)
[![](screenshots/sundial.png){width=80%}](https://reproducible.shinyapps.io/sundial/)

 * Set start and finish times based on location & sun position.
 * Works for low and medium latitudes 
 * Useful for calibrating remote arrays 

<br/>
<br/>

